<section id=3D"S3" class=3D"ltx_section">
<h2 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_section">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_section">3 </span>Empirical Study</h2>

<div id=3D"S3.p1" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S3.p1.1" class=3D"ltx_p">This section presents the design of our e=
mpirical study, which aims to evaluate whether the student model deeply mim=
ics the teacher=E2=80=99s predictive behavior and internal representations =
during knowledge distillation by assessing its adversarial robustness. We h=
ypothesize that if the student model deeply mimics the teacher during knowl=
edge distillation, it should exhibit adversarial performance comparable to =
the teacher=E2=80=99s. Any substantial deviation in robustness would indica=
te that the student model fails to deeply mimic the teacher=E2=80=99s predi=
ctive behavior and internal representations. We first describe the selected=
 knowledge distillation approaches for code-language models, followed by de=
tails on datasets, models, adversarial attack approaches, and the experimen=
tal setup. Finally, we outline the evaluation metrics used in the analysis =
and present the corresponding results in the following section.</p>
</div>
<section id=3D"S3.SS1" class=3D"ltx_subsection">
<h3 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection">3.1 </span>Study Design</h3>

<section id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1" class=3D"ltx_subsubsection">
<h4 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_subsubsection">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsubsection">3.1.1 </span>Knowledge Distil=
lation Approaches</h4>

<div id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1" class=3D"ltx_p">In recent years, several knowled=
ge distillation (KD) approaches have been proposed for language models of c=
ode, including <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.1" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_i=
talic">Compressor</span> <cite class=3D"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">Shi<sp=
an class=3D"ltx_text ltx_bib_etal"> et al.</span> [<a href=3D"https://arxiv=
.org/html/2511.05476#bib.bib6" title=3D"Compressing pre-trained models of c=
ode into 3 mb" class=3D"ltx_ref">2023</a>]</cite>, <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.=
p1.1.2" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">AVATAR</span> <cite class=3D"ltx=
_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">Shi<span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_bib_etal"> et al.<=
/span> [<a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2511.05476#bib.bib8" title=3D"Gre=
ening large language models of code" class=3D"ltx_ref">2024a</a>]</cite>, <=
span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.3" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">SODA</spa=
n> <cite class=3D"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">Chen<span class=3D"ltx_text =
ltx_bib_etal"> et al.</span> [<a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2511.05476#=
bib.bib114" title=3D"Smaller but better: self-paced knowledge distillation =
for lightweight yet effective lcms" class=3D"ltx_ref">2025</a>]</cite>, <sp=
an id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.4" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MORPH</span=
> <cite class=3D"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">Panichella [<a href=3D"https:=
//arxiv.org/html/2511.05476#bib.bib29" title=3D"Metamorphic-based many-obje=
ctive distillation of llms for code-related tasks" class=3D"ltx_ref">2025</=
a>]</cite>, and <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.5" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_=
italic">PIONEER</span> <cite class=3D"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">Liu<span=
 class=3D"ltx_text ltx_bib_etal"> et al.</span> [<a href=3D"https://arxiv.o=
rg/html/2511.05476#bib.bib31" title=3D"PIONEER: improving the robustness of=
 student models when compressing pre-trained models of code" class=3D"ltx_r=
ef">2026</a>]</cite>. In this study, we select <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1=
.6" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Compressor</span>, <span id=3D"S3.SS=
1.SSS1.p1.1.7" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">AVATAR</span>, and <span =
id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.8" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MORPH</span> a=
s our KD approaches to generate student models, as the replication package =
for <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.9" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">SODA=
</span> is not fully available<span id=3D"footnote4" class=3D"ltx_note ltx_=
role_footnote"><sup class=3D"ltx_note_mark">4</sup><span class=3D"ltx_note_=
outer"><span class=3D"ltx_note_content"><sup class=3D"ltx_note_mark">4</sup=
><span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_note">4</span>https://shorturl.at/Se0f7</sp=
an></span></span>. Furthermore, both <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1.10" class=
=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MORPH</span> and <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p1.1=
.11" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">PIONEER</span> incorporate robustne=
