<div id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1" class=3D"ltx_p"><span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.1" =
class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Compressor</span> uses the genetic algor=
ithm to identify a simplified architecture that maximizes <span id=3D"S3.SS=
1.SSS1.p3.1.2" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">giga floating-point opera=
tions</span> (GFLOPs) while minimizing <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.3" clas=
s=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">model size</span> within a fixed memory budg=
et. <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.4" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">AVAT=
AR</span> compresses language models of code into deployable versions by jo=
intly optimizing <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.5" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font=
_italic">model size</span>, <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.6" class=3D"ltx_te=
xt ltx_font_italic">inference latency</span>, <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.=
7" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">energy consumption</span>, and <span =
id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.8" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">accuracy</span=
>. It formulates the problem as a multi-objective configuration tuning task=
, using an SMT solver to define the search space and a tailored optimizatio=
n algorithm to identify a Pareto-optimal set of configurations for the stud=
ent model. Based on the <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.9" class=3D"ltx_text l=
tx_font_italic">AVATAR</span>, <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1.10" class=3D"lt=
x_text ltx_font_italic">MORPH</span> considers <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS1.p3.1=
.11" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">metamorphic robustness</span> a cru=
cial property for multi-objective optimization in architecture selection fo=
r the student model. In addition, it distills knowledge from the teacher mo=
del not only on the soft targets but also on the metamorphic code=E2=80=99s=
 outputs, assuming the teacher model always produces correct outputs for th=
e metamorphic code. Subsequently, knowledge distillation is performed by mi=
nimizing the loss between the soft targets produced by the teacher model an=
d those generated by the student model. For example, <span id=3D"S3.SS1.SSS=
1.p3.1.12" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Compressor</span> employs the=
 KL divergence loss function, defined as follows:</p>
</div>
