<section id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px2" class=3D"ltx_paragraph">
<h5 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_font_bold ltx_title_paragraph">Rationale</h5>

<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px2.p1" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px2.p1.1" class=3D"ltx_p">Although the teacher and stu=
dent models may produce the same predicted label, their underlying probabil=
ity distributions can differ substantially. Our empirical observations (Fig=
ure 3(a)) reveal such differences, as measured by the Kullback=E2=80=93Leib=
ler divergence metric (e.g., 0.6177), suggesting that prediction agreement =
(<span id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px2.p1.1.1" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_bold">MR1</=
span>) alone is insufficient to ensure behavioral fidelity.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px3" class=3D"ltx_paragraph">
<h5 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_font_bold ltx_title_paragraph">Evaluation metric=
</h5>

<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px3.p1" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px3.p1.1" class=3D"ltx_p">To quantify the difference b=
etween the two probability distributions, we use the Kullback=E2=80=93Leibl=
er divergence, as defined in =E2=80=9C(<a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/25=
11.05476#S2.E1" title=3D"In 2.6 Kullback=E2=80=93Leibler Divergence =E2=80=
=A3 2 Preliminaries =E2=80=A3 A Metamorphic Testing Perspective on Knowledg=
e Distillation for Language Models of Code: Does the Student Deeply Mimic t=
he Teacher?" class=3D"ltx_ref"><span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">1</span=
></a>)=E2=80=9D. Given a tolerance <math id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS2.Px3.p1.1.m1" cla=
ss=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"\delta=3D0.5" display=3D"inline" intent=3D":lite=
ral"><semantics><mrow><mi>=CE=B4</mi><mo>=3D</mo><mn>0.5</mn></mrow><annota=
tion encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\delta=3D0.5</annotation></semantics></=
math> (Inspired by sigmoid-based methods for binary classification <cite cl=
ass=3D"ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">LeCun<span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_bib_et=
al"> et al.</span> [<a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2511.05476#bib.bib48"=
 title=3D"Deep learning" class=3D"ltx_ref">2015</a>]</cite>), we then count=
 the test instances for which MR2 holds:</p>
</div>
