<section id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2" class=3D"ltx_paragraph">
<h5 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_font_bold ltx_title_paragraph">Rationale</h5>

<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2.p1" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2.p1.3" class=3D"ltx_p">A Top-1 agreement alone may =
mask cases where <math id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2.p1.1.m1" class=3D"ltx_Math" al=
ttext=3D"M_{S}" display=3D"inline" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><msub><mi=
>M</mi><mi>S</mi></msub><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">M_{S}</a=
nnotation></semantics></math> is hesitant while <math id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2=
.p1.2.m2" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"M_{T}" display=3D"inline" intent=3D=
":literal"><semantics><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>T</mi></msub><annotation encoding=
=3D"application/x-tex">M_{T}</annotation></semantics></math> is decisive. O=
ur manual investigation (Figure 3(a)) revealed that large confidence gaps (=
e.g., <math id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2.p1.3.m3" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"|0=
.99-0.51|=3D0.48" display=3D"inline" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><mrow><=
mrow><mo stretchy=3D"false">|</mo><mrow><mn>0.99</mn><mo>=E2=88=92</mo><mn>=
0.51</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=3D"false">|</mo></mrow><mo>=3D</mo><mn>0.48</m=
n></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">|0.99-0.51|=3D0.48</ann=
otation></semantics></math>) often coincide with divergent reasoning, even =
when predictions align. By enforcing both label and confidence alignment on=
 high-certainty inputs, <span id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px2.p1.3.1" class=3D"ltx_te=
xt ltx_font_bold">MR3</span> probes a deeper layer of behavioral fidelity.<=
/p>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS3.Px3" class=3D"ltx_paragraph">
<h5 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_font_bold ltx_title_paragraph">Evaluation metric=
