<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p3" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p3.1" class=3D"ltx_p">A lower ECA score (<math id=
=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p3.1.m1" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"\text{ECA}\in[0,=
1]" display=3D"inline" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><mrow><mtext>ECA</mte=
xt><mo>=E2=88=88</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=3D"false">[</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo=
><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=3D"false">]</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=
=3D"application/x-tex">\text{ECA}\in[0,1]</annotation></semantics></math>) =
indicates that the student model=E2=80=99s calibration behavior closely ali=
gns with that of the teacher model. Conversely, a higher ECA score reflects=
 greater divergence between the two models=E2=80=99 calibration profiles.</=
p>
</div>
<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p4" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p4.3" class=3D"ltx_p"><span id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.=
p4.3.1" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Violation rate computation:</span>=
 To compute the violation rate of a metamorphic relation <math id=3D"S4.SS2=
.SSS4.Px3.p4.1.m1" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"\text{MR}_{k}" display=3D"=
inline" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><msub><mtext>MR</mtext><mi>k</mi></m=
sub><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\text{MR}_{k}</annotation></=
semantics></math>, we use the complement of its hold rate. Let <math id=3D"=
S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p4.2.m2" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"\text{HoldRate}_{\te=
xt{MR}_{k}}\in[0,1]" display=3D"inline" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><mro=
w><msub><mtext>HoldRate</mtext><msub><mtext>MR</mtext><mi>k</mi></msub></ms=
