<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p6" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p6.1" class=3D"ltx_p">This formulation enables us =
to quantify the extent to which a student model deviates from the behaviora=
l invariants defined by each metamorphic relation. Higher violation rates i=
ndicate greater behavioral drift from the teacher model.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p7" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.p7.2" class=3D"ltx_p"><span id=3D"S4.SS2.SSS4.Px3.=
p7.2.1" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_bold">Expected Behaviour: </span>A stude=
nt model is considered behavior-preserving if, for every test input, the st=
