<div id=3D"S4.SS3.SSS2.p7" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S4.SS3.SSS2.p7.2" class=3D"ltx_p"><span id=3D"S4.SS3.SSS2.p7.2.1" =
class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_bold">MR4 violation:</span> Table <a href=3D"htt=
ps://arxiv.org/html/2511.05476#S4.T3" title=3D"Table 3 =E2=80=A3 4.3.2 Eval=
uation Results =E2=80=A3 4.3 MetaCompress Evaluation =E2=80=A3 4 Approach: =
MetaCompress Framework =E2=80=A3 A Metamorphic Testing Perspective on Knowl=
edge Distillation for Language Models of Code: Does the Student Deeply Mimi=
c the Teacher?" class=3D"ltx_ref"><span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">3</s=
pan></a> presents the calibration deviation between teacher and student mod=
els across three knowledge distillation techniques for varying bin sizes (<=
math id=3D"S4.SS3.SSS2.p7.1.m1" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"B=3D10,15,20"=
 display=3D"inline" intent=3D":literal"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mo>=3D<=
/mo><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mro=
w><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">B=3D10,15,20</annotation></sem=
antics></math>). The results reveal that the calibration alignment varies n=
otably across tasks and distillation strategies. For the clone detection ta=
sk, all student models maintain near-perfect calibration consistency with t=
heir teachers, with deviation values below 0.04, indicating that the studen=
ts effectively preserve the teachers=E2=80=99 confidence distributions. In =
contrast, the vulnerability prediction task exhibits substantially higher d=
eviations marked by dark gray cells, up to 0.14 for CodeBERT and 0.11 for G=
raphCodeBERT, demonstrating that the student models=E2=80=99 probabilistic =
calibration diverges considerably from that of the teachers. These results =
highlight that although student models may achieve comparable accuracy, the=
ir confidence calibration can differ sharply, underscoring <span id=3D"S4.S=
S3.SSS2.p7.2.2" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MetaCompress</span> =E2=
=80=99s ability to capture nuanced behavioral discrepancies beyond what tra=
ditional evaluation metrics can reveal. We further examine the sensitivity =
of <span id=3D"S4.SS3.SSS2.p7.2.3" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_bold">MR4</sp=
an> to different bin sizes and observe that variations in <math id=3D"S4.SS=
3.SSS2.p7.2.m2" class=3D"ltx_Math" alttext=3D"B" display=3D"inline" intent=
=3D":literal"><semantics><mi>B</mi><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-te=
x">B</annotation></semantics></math> had a negligible effect on overall vio=
lation rates, confirming the metric=E2=80=99s stability.</p>
</div>
